  "bib_entries": {
    "156685578": {
      "title": "The economic significance of insurance markets in developing countries",
      "abstract": "The importance of the relationship between financial development and economic growth is recognized in the economic literature. Recent evidence suggests that the developing countries have a supply-leading causality pattern of development. Property-Liability insurance like other financial services has grown in quantitative importance as part of the general development of financial institutions. This article investigates empirically the relationship between property-liability insurance premiums and economic and financial development. A model is specified for property-liability insurance demand and it is tested with a cross-section of 55 developing countries."
    }
